   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Collect Crypto Prices Using the `requests` Library"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set current amount of crypto assets\n",
    "My_BTC = 1.2\n",
    "My_ETH = 5.3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Response [200]>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Crypto API URLs\n",
    "BTC_URL = \"https://api.alternative.me/v2/ticker/Bitcoin/?convert=CAD\"\n",
    "ETH_URL = \"https://api.alternative.me/v2/ticker/Ethereum/?convert=CAD\"\n",
    "requests.get(BTC_URL)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The current value of your 1.2 BTC is $15940.73\n",
      "The current value of your 5.3 ETH is $2072.25\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Fetch current BTC price\n",
    "Fetch_Data = requests.get(BTC_URL).json()\n",
    "Price_BTC = Fetch_Data['data']['1']['quotes']['USD']['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fetch current ETH price\n",
    "Fetch_Data = requests.get(ETH_URL).json()\n",
    "Price_ETH = Fetch_Data['data']['1027']['quotes']['USD']['price']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute current value of my crpto\n",
    "My_BTC_Value = My_BTC * Price_BTC\n",
    "My_ETH_Value = My_ETH * Price_ETH\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print current crypto wallet balance\n",
    "print(f\"The current value of your {My_BTC} BTC is ${My_BTC_Value:0.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"The current value of your {My_ETH} ETH is ${My_ETH_Value:0.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Collect Investments Data Using Alpaca: `SPY` (stocks) and `AGG` (bonds)"
   ]

   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Current amount of shares\n",
    "My_SPY = 50\n",

   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},

    "\n",
    "# Create the Alpaca API object\n",
    "Alpaca = tradeapi.REST(\n",
    "    Alpaca_API_Key,\n",
    "    Alpaca_Secret_Key,\n",
    "    api_version=\"v2\")"

    "# Format current date as ISO format\n",
    "Now = pd.Timestamp(\"2020-10-27\", tz=\"America/New_York\").isoformat()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set the tickers\n",
    "tickers = [\"AGG\", \"SPY\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set timeframe to '1D' for Alpaca API\n",
    "timeframe = \"1D\"\n",

    "    tickers,\n",
    "    timeframe,\n",
    "    start = Now,\n",
    "    end = Now\n",

    "# Set monthly household income\n",
    "Monthly_Income = 12000\n",

    "# Create savings DataFrame\n",
    "All_Savings = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    [\n",
    "        [My_BTC_Value + My_ETH_Value],\n",
    "        [My_SPY_Value + My_AGG_Value]\n",
    "    ],\n",

    "    columns = [\"amount\"]\n",

    "\n",
    "# Display savings DataFrame\n",

    "# Set ideal emergency fund\n",
    "Emergency_Fund = Monthly_Income * 3\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate total amount of savings\n",
    "Total_Savings = All_Savings[\"amount\"][\"Cryptos Value\"] + \\\n",
    "    All_Savings[\"amount\"][\"Stocks Value\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Validate saving health\n",
    "if Total_Savings > Emergency_Fund:\n",
    "    print(\"Congratulations for having enough money in this Fund!\")\n",
    "elif Total_Savings == Emergency_Fund:\n",
    "    print(\"Congratulations for reaching your Financial Goals\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"You are ${(Emergency_Fund - Total_Savings):0.2f} away from reaching your Goal\")"

   "source": [
    "### Calculate the expected portfolio return at the 95% lower and upper confidence intervals based on a `$20,000` initial investment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "There is a 95% chance that an initial investment of $20000 in the portfolio over the next 30 years will end within in the range of $43265.38847713973 and $330875.70394555584\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Set initial investment\n",
    "initial_investment = 20000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use the lower and upper `95%` confidence intervals to calculate the range of the possible outcomes of our $20,000\n",
    "ci_lower = Summary_Statistics[8] * initial_investment\n",
    "ci_upper = Summary_Statistics[9] * initial_investment\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print results\n",
    "print(f\"There is a 95% chance that an initial investment of ${initial_investment} in the portfolio\"\n",
    "      f\" over the next 30 years will end within in the range of\"\n",
    "      f\" ${ci_lower} and ${ci_upper}\")"
   ]
